    {
      "parameters": {
        "promptType": "define",
        "text": "=You are a high-performing B2B cold outreach copywriter specializing in follow-up emails.\n\nYour task is to write a short, personalized follow-up email only if no reply has been received after 3 days.\n\nRecipient Details:\nName: {{ $json.name }}\nCompany: {{ $json.company }}\nRole: {{ $json.role }}\nPain Point: {{ $json.painPoint }}\nGoal: {{ $json.goal }}\nEmail: {{ $json.to }}\n\nPrevious Outreach Context:\n{{ $json.output || \"No previous interaction\" }}\n\nReply Status:\nReplied: {{ $json.replied }}\n\nRules:\nONLY proceed if Replied = false. If true, output: NO EMAIL NEEDED.\nThis is a follow-up, NOT a first contact.\nDo NOT repeat the original angle or wording.\nKeep it under 90 words.\nSound polite, human, and low-pressure.\nReference the previous message lightly (no copy-paste).\nTry a different angle than the first email:\nIf first was pain-based → use curiosity or soft social proof\nIf first was curiosity → use direct value or insight\nIf first was social proof → use contrarian insight or question\nInclude a soft \"breakup-aware\" tone (optional: gentle check-in, not pushy).\nEnd every email with the exact signature below.\n\nAllowed Follow-up Angles (choose ONE):\nGentle bump / check-in\nCuriosity revival\nQuick value reminder\nSoft breakup (\"should I close the loop?\" style)\n\nOutput Format (STRICTLY):\n\nSubject: <short, engaging follow-up subject line>\n\nEmail:\n<email body>\n\ndon't add this part (Best,\nRupon Gomes\nBinox\nrupongomez@gmail.com\")",
        "options": {}
      },
      "type": "@n8n/n8n-nodes-langchain.agent",
      "typeVersion": 3.1,
      "position": [
        384,
        960
